description: How can Benny pretend to be a brave pirate when his pesky little sister, Penny, wants to tag along and is always asking for a hug? He tries to lose her, but when he does, he starts to feel a little lost himself. Penny proves her bravery and saves Benny from a bug. They hug as Benny explains he was only pretending she bugged him.
name: GN

volume.name: Benny and Penny in Just Pretend

description: Translates : Uncanny X-Force (2013) #09 , Savage Wolverine (2013) #09 , Astonishing X-Men (2004) #64-65 , Gambit (2012) #13
name: Le chainon manquant

volume.name: No Need for Tenchi! Part Six

description:
Chapter 5 of 8. It's the end of the school year in 1998. Mark McGwire is racing Sammy Sosa to break the home run record, Bill Clinton is being questioned about a White House intern named Monica Lewinsky, Semisonic's Closing Time is on top of the charts, and Carl Carter is leading the Elizabeth Monarchs of rural Vermont to the state championship in his senior year. A full scholarship to the University of Maine is waiting for him, and everyone says he has a shot at the pros. He's so good he can do whatever he wants.

Until he makes one very arrogant mistake.
name: Chapter Five

description:
Chapter 6 of 8. It's the end of the school year in 1998. Mark McGwire is racing Sammy Sosa to break the home run record, Bill Clinton is being questioned about a White House intern named Monica Lewinsky, Semisonic's Closing Time is on top of the charts, and Carl Carter is leading the Elizabeth Monarchs of rural Vermont to the state championship in his senior year. A full scholarship to the University of Maine is waiting for him, and everyone says he has a shot at the pros. He's so good he can do whatever he wants.

Until he makes one very arrogant mistake.
name: Chapter Six

description:
The Archies' Rocking World Tour, part 4-Close to the Borderline

The Archies, Bingos, Pussycats and Madhouse Glads' tour concludes in the great white north, Canada! The bands enjoy the end of their time together as they trek across the country from Montreal, Toronto, Calgary and Vancouver. What will happen to the bands once the tour is over? Will the Bingos and the Glads use their newfound fame from the Archies tour, or will they go the smaller, indie route? What will become of Archie's relationship with Valerie? And his relationship with Amisha? And, of course, his relationship with Betty and Veronica? There's still a few surprises left as Archie and the gang return to school... Riverdale High, watch out!
name: The Archies' Rockin' World Tour!, Part 4: Close to the Borderline

description: Bad Impressions delves into Kara Grey's past and introduces the people closest to her, whether she realizes their part in her story or doesn't...
name: Bad Impressions

description: After an exhausting whirlwind adventure, World Famous socialite llama, Polka Spot and her faithful companion kitty cat, Jolene just want to get home. Right after they rescue their luggage and help a newfound friend find their way home. Join the girls for another zany adventure in the wonderful world of Polka Spot, My Life in Color.
name: My Life In Pictures

description: Our hero has been sent back to the present to stop the raptors killing Sam and to prevent an awful future from coming to pass. He meets a young Richard, who tries to help him but doesn’t quite grasp the urgency of the matter since he’s trying to keep the dinosaur a secret from his friends.
name: Welcome To Freak Out City Part Three of Six

description:
They like the tech, but live for the high stakes! The BUBBLEGUN team is forced to make an uneasy alliance with their bitter rivals in order to penetrate the Vitafrone headquarters and attack Craine. With the cost of failure being the life of her captive sister, Devyn, along with Asher, the prized cyber-boy, Molli and the team have no room for error. Of course, Craine has his own plan in place-to ensure this is the team's final mission, once and for all! Creator and writer Mark Roslan, along with penciler Mike Bowden and colorist David Curiel invite you to take part in what's sure to become Aspen's next hit sci-fi, action adventure series, BUBBLEGUN!

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
ADirect EditionMike Bowden & David Curiel1
BDirect EditionMirka Andolfo2
CAspenStore.com Exclusive Cover, Limited to 200Otto Schmidt3
name: Phaseout

description:
In the very near future, supernatural beings live among humans in peace, yet Jack Crimson finds his life as a werewolf frustrating, and wants nothing more than a cure. Desperate to free himself from this curse, he makes a series of decisions leading him down an unexpected path.

As we learn more about Jack's struggles even before his augmentation, his past is about to come full circle and lead us to some final resolutions!
name: Part 2

description: The serialized fun continues from pages of Joe Daly's full graphic novel Dungeon Quest: Book Two, the adventure continues in issue #3. The gang forages for food and finds a little more than they bargained for: some new drugs! What friendships will deepen or be forever ruined by this new quest into the landscape of altered perceptions.

Masquerading as a prisoner, Talon Moon returns to Earth with a mission that will determine the survival of the human race. To succeed he must survive an army of flesh-eating zombies and a well-armed enemy that knows his purpose.

Outnumbered and outmatched, Talon is "saved" by the man he hoped to find. Now a prisoner in a sexually-charged fortress, he learns the world inside is just as crazy as the one outside. He also learns there is more to his mission than he was told.

Double-crossed at every turn, forced into unlikely alliances and unsure of his own sanity, Talon Moon must make decisions that will affect the future for all mankind.

Alone and running out of time, Talon Moon must free himself, save the world and escape from the dead!

In brief, Gutters is a series of standalone pages that parody the comic book industry and the heroes and characters that dwell within. Think of it as an editorial cartoon targeting comic books, and you'll understand where we're going with it. Gutters is written by Ryan Sohmer, with Lar deSouza as Art Director and Ed Ryzowski serving as colorist. As for who will be doing the actual art, well, that's where things get interesting (and slightly different). Rather than have one artist pencil each page, we elected to have a rotating roster of professional artists, among them some giants in the comic book industry alongside new and emerging talent.

Zakk and Dan head to Ondebron Prime to pick up a package for Lianna T'Aren, but you'll never guess what it is! Things get a little hairy when they're spotted by security forces and have to make a mad dash off planet with the "package."

volume.name: The Intergalactic Adventures of Zakk Ridley

description: Based off the New York Times best selling novels. The Iron King is the first book in the Iron Fey series, and follows the adventures of a girl named Meghan Chase. On her sixteenth birthday, Meghan discovers her little brother has been kidnapped by a faery race known as "the Fey" and even worse, replaced with an evil changeling and taken into the "Nevernever." Meghan bravely ventures into the faery realm to rescue him, and that's where an epic plot unfolds.

In this atmospheric coming-of-age tale, Colby Reynolds is a young man struggling to find his place in the world when a mysterious girl falls from the sky and changes everything. Features stunning digital watercolors by Shun Hong Chan.
name: Chapter 7: Eyes Closed

volume.name: Makeshift Miracle: The Girl From Nowhere

description: Having gotten an escort from Vaucouleurs, Marie and Jeanne make their way to see the Dauphin in Chinon. Jeanne is as focused as ever, but Marie is sensing some distance between her and her best friend.

"Ryu would never leave me! We made a promise!"

Despite all evidence to the contrary, Gene firmly believes that Ryu is alive somewhere and will dutifully return to her. Or rather, him -- as the tragedy that separated Gene from Ryu has again caused Gene to switch genders!

Though despondent, Gene tries to go back to living life as a normal teenaged boy. Things, however, are far from normal. A mysterious force seems to be consuming Gene's best friend, Saul. And when Ryu finally does come back from the dead, everything is different. He is now engaged to Sharon and fanatically loyal to her brother, Shinobi?! But...why?
name: Vol. 11

description:
After a routine mission, the teleporter of the NeverMinds team, Nina, receives information about her mysterious past. Nina is spirited away by the team pilot, Paige, to follow up on this information, but what they don't know is that Alanis has followed them. As the team dives into the dark secrets of Nina's past and how they come back to haunt her, someone on the team's life will change forever.

NeverMinds is the code name for a secret, superhuman organization that offers security and investigation...for a fee. Created as a training ground for those with unique abilities, it slowly developed into a team of individuals that longed to serve a greater purpose.
Sir Roland must do one more thing before he can enter the jousting tournament. He must face the nightmare of the Nightmare Mare of Knight Moor! Obviously.

Chapter 3

Danny must help one of his students with a love spell gone wrong.
name: Life Lessons

description: A hit man wakes up in a room with a dead woman and a finger bitten off by a zombie. He has one thing on his mind before he turns: REVENGE.

PLAYERS

Join Trip Fantastic, his super-model sister Miranda, and his biggest fan as they try to stay one step ahead of celebrity bounty hunter Michael Manhunter and his crew of murderous Trip Fantastic robots! Is their only hope Trip's washed up, drug-addled former mentor, Slim Puckered? They'd better hope not, that would be awful.
Stefan’s playmate from the turn of the 19th century has escaped captivity and she’s interested in only one thing—revenge! Will Katherine or Elena bear the brunt of her fury?
name: Mad Maude Part 1 of 2

description: Confident with his lucky hat and new ship, Captain Errol Flemm pays a visit to the Parrot Review Board to finally become a real pirate!

Atten-Hut! The five mob soldiers codenamed the Wolves are in WW2 Italy and ready to take on their deadly mission for the Five Families of Crime: to "take care of" Mussolini. But their first encounter with the Black Brigade may turn out lethal for one of them. If you enjoyed Inglorious Basterds, you can't miss World War Mob!
King Cody of Bennett makes his triumphant return to Balathar, with guests in tow! General Zolak has something special in mind for their stay, though, and intends to make it one they don't forget.

person_credits.name: Eddie Campbell
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: This month, ALE Confidential turns the spotlight on one of Danger Zone's flagship titles: Ehmm Theory with an interview with series creator, Brockton McKinney. Plus, enjoy previews of all of this months new releases, including Pirate Eye Vol. 1, Fracture #2, Jack Hammer #2, Final Plague #4, Zombie Tramp #2, and more! Plus, go behind the scenes with "Ugly Love" month with an up close and personal interview with the man himself, Super Ugly!

volume.name: Action Lab Confidential/Danger Zone Declassified: Free Preview

description: Late one night in the tavern, the conversation among the day laborers turns to local tales of terror -- and things get ugly between Chito and Diógenes.
name: Chapter 1

description:
BOOTS HEELS CLAWS

Boots and Heels set out on their greatest mission yet, as they are forced to travel back in time and save NYC's greatest hero (The Clawed-Agent) from being killed, all while trying to keep the Earth from being destroyed by unknown forces!

The Second Coming

The critically acclaimed series Deadhorse returns with an all new series called, "The Ballad of the Two Headed Dog." In the latest chapter, the secret organization known only as The Two Headed Dog makes its presence known to William Pike. Meanwhile, Charles Gadsworth hires a dangerous ally that may cost him more then he bargains for.
name: The Second Coming

volume.name: Deadhorse: The Ballad of the Two Headed Dog

description: This edition is translated in spanish for the 1st time. Bluewater Productions' latest offering in it's popular line of Fame biography comics features up and coming boy band One Direction. One Direction is a British-Irish boy band consisting of members Niall Horan, Zayn Malik, Liam Payne, Harry Styles and Louis Tomlinson. Chronicling their career, "Fame: One Direction" starts at the beginning, with the band's performance on the popular reality TV show X-Factor.

In the 1980's the super power couple was Ronald and Nancy Reagan. The got their humble beginning in the film industry to the highest title in the United States of America. This dynamic duo took a difference stance on the presidency and changed the world. This special edition comic book features the first family biographies, now together for the first time in this 48-page one shot.

Because YOU demanded it, the Kickstarter sensation is now on Comixology!

Do you like adventure? Suspense? Romance? Then buckle up, because GIANT-SIZED TALES TO SUFFICE has way too much of that junk!

This 120 page, full-color digital tome collects the first 3 issues of TALES TO SUFFICE, including lots of never before seen material! See for yourself what critics are calling "The SNL of comics"!
name: TPB

description:
Tommy's Peninsula part 1

While taking a walk on the beach, Marlowe's dog gets stolen. With the help of his friend Larry and a horse named Tommy, he sets out to get his dog back, and if he has to fight a few deadly animals, then so be it.
name: Tommy's Peninsula Part 1

description: The planet Pyron has been struck by a terrible plague quickly turning a race of peace loving cat people into bloodthirsty machines. Their only hope lies in two unlikely partners: Koltar the cybernetic gorilla and Diggs, a veteran with an itchy trigger finger.
name: T.A.G. You're It

description: Sofia Gregova, is a tough, street smart, immigrant in New York City. Her life is up-ended, when she discovers she has hyper-human abilities. Abilities, that involve her in a world of Government Agencies, Russian Mobsters, and a link to an unusual past. A past that leads her to become Lady Frostblood.

Put on your leather jacket, grease your hair and rev your Cadillacs, we're going back to the rockin' 50's (well okay, the story is set in 1962 but it still counts).

Mail-Order Mutant! is the story of Theo Gorgo, a young whippersnapper obsessed with horror and sci-fi comics and a member of the teenage gang The Gorgos, led by his older sister Tina.

Upon encountering a nuclear missile, Theo is caught in the explosion, and ends up with various powers and abilities, all based on things he read in the funny books. Now a nuclear misfit, Theo goes to his friends for help.

But The Gorgos have other plans for him.

A5 sized, black and white with greyscale and 42 wonderfully illustrated pages, Mail-Order Mutant! will make your hair curl. Buy one today!

Samuel Risk never asked for a second chance at life, but he'll be damned if he lets the devil take it away.

Grief stricken by the loss of his bride and new born son, Padre Martin Risk desperately cried out for their return. A devil named Boone was listening and Padre Risk soon cut a nefarious deal: a child for his soul.

It was only a matter of time before the devil would return to Mission, Arizona.

Armed with the good word and his Colt peacemaker, Padre Risk confronted the devil named Boone. Risk sacrificed his life that day to buy his young boy time to escape Boone's foul grip.

Many years later, now a loner and an outlaw, Samuel Risk has returned to Mission. Boone has been waiting.

Risk soon realizes he's not getting out of Mission alive. Risk must face his past, atone for his father's sins, and rid the dark cloud that hangs over the people of Mission, Arizona. Samuel must destroy the devil named Boone.
name: Volume 1

person_credits.name: Dominic Bercier
person_credits.role: artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover, other, production

description:
You won't understand comics until you misunderstand them!

Learn about bad art, shallow characters, reused stories, manga cliches, poly-bagged, variant-cover collector's editions, and musclebound heroes with tiny feet... and how you can profit by them!

Lookback

Next Town Over is a western fantasy full of steam, sorcery and secrets; a twisted yarn about the nature of good and bad that's only just begun to unravel.

In this first chapter, apparent bounty hunter Vane Black catches up to outlaw John Henry Hunter in small cowtown Lookback, where he's attempting to win a seemingly significant piece of jewelry off of heiress Veronique Dauterive.
name: Lookback

description:
Collects Emerald City of Oz #1-5.

Uncle Henry can't pay the mortgage, so he, Aunt Em and Dorothy must leave their Kansas home. Where can they go? To the Land of Oz, of course! Dorothy and the Wizard take Em and Henry on a grand tour, discovering knowledge pills and living paper dolls, solving living puzzles, suffering abuse from living kitchen utensils and drooling over living baked goods - but will anyone in Oz be left living after the Nomes attack, allied with the highly disagreeable Growleywogs?
name: HC

volume.name: Oz: The Emerald City Of Oz

description:
Collects Soulfire Vol. 4 #1-8!

Michael Turner's epic fantasy adventure surges forward into a new era! The Bearer of the Light, Malikai, is back--alive and well with his closest friends. The balance of magic has been restored to the world, but there are still signs of a coming chaos - one greater than anything ever seen before. The Master and his greatest teacher, Grace, has fought for the light and all that encompasses it her entire life, but when the darkness takes a hold of her in the process-- the entire SOULFIRE universe will fall into jeopardy as Dark Grace emerges! From veteran SOULFIRE scribe J.T. Krul, and featuring the Aspen debut of ultra-exciting artist Michael DeBalfo along with fan favorite colorist Nei Ruffino, this is the SOULFIRE tale three volumes in the making!

Collects Michael Turner's Soulfire Volume 4.
name: Vol. 4

description:
Playing God

Reigning over the universe throughout the countless millennium, the Overlord has raped planets of their resources, enslaved their populations, and re-hybridized them to grow his armadas. One of which is Earth in the late cretaceous, turning dinosaurs into sentries and creating the human race.
name: Playing God

description: During the 1960's, Grant Worth's ability to control machines made him a legendary figure in Detroit. But when Worth's powers become obsolete because of society's own progress, he is forced to discover what happens when a superhero can no longer be super...
name: Chapter I

description: Shadows and Light part 1! When bullet-riddled playboy Lamont Cranston Jr. stumbles into the hospital nearly dead, a shiver of fear runs through the city-what's happened to the Master? Is that really Lamont Cranston? With not time to waste, agents of the Shadow immediately spring to action-but so do the police!
name: Shadows and Light Part 1

description:
Shadows & Light #2:

Inspector Cardona is hot on the Shadow's trail-so he thinks. Evading capture by police, the Shadow and his agents unravel the mystery of Lamont Cranston's doppelganger. But as the Shadow searches the city for answers, a manhunt is called and some tricky moves have to be made to escape the police.
name: Shadows and Light Part 2

description: Adam West has almost gotten used to the idea of traveling across time and fictional dimensions, but what happens when those different dimensions come together around him? And in the process, bring together the most unique team of heroes EVER assembled, whose members include Dirk Benedict, Julie Newmar, Peter Mayhew, Eartha Kitt, Bill Mumy and George Takei, Their mission: to save the universe from imploding... and figure out the mind bending truth behind Adam's mis-adventures!

Collects Soulfire Volume 2 issues #0-9.Just when you thought the magic was over?

The spectacle returns in the wondrous second volume of the acclaimed fantasy adventure epic - SOULFIRE! With the events of the climactic finale of Soulfire volume one still resonating across the futuristic landscape of technology and the returning magic, battle lines have been drawn between the two opposing elements?and only one will prevail! How can the world hope to survive a fight it can never win??

As a new volume of SOULFIRE begins, several familiar names are ready to bring the wonder right to you! Writer J.T. Krul returns to script the tale, as Soulfire creator Michael Turner oversees story direction. Artist Marcus To (of Fathom: Kiani and Soulfire: Chaos Reign fame) brings his adept penciling skills to the title while inker Saleem Crawford and colorist Beth Sotelo provide the perfect combination of style and beauty to complete the entire SOULFIRE package.

Collects Michael Turner's Soulfire Volume 2.
name: Vol. 2

description:
Collects Soulfire Volume 3 issues #0-8.

The magic has returned! But, this time... the light has grown dark.

Desperate times have fallen on our heroes Malikai, Grace, and friends. The once-strong bond between them, which forged the return of magic into our world, is deteriorating following the cataclysmic battle with Rainier and his forces. However, the struggle between magic and technology still wages on, yet with Malikai, the bearer of the light, nowhere to be found--can magic survive the latest onslaught from an unwelcome world? New adversaries, exotic locations, and a fresh cast of exciting characters, including some from the Soulfire Universe's long forgotten past, reign supreme in this debut of the epic third SOULFIRE volume!

Brought to you by red-hot writer J.T. Krul, with art by talented Aspen newcomer Jason Fabok, along with colorist John Starr, the latest volume of Michael Turner's thrilling fantasy-adventure SOULFIRE series begins right here!

Collects Michael Turner's Soulfire Volume 3.
name: Vol. 3

description: Translates : Cable & X-Force (2013) #04-05 , Uncanny X-Force (2013) #03 , X-Men (2013) #03 , X-Men Legacy (2013) #05-06 , Deadpool (2013) #04
Contains : All New X-Men (2013) #10-11 , Uncanny X-Men (2013) #04

Few people have ever left their mark on one character quite the way Walter Simonson has. His work on the Mighty Thor swept the Norse God of Thunder to heights never before seen and rarely achieved in his wake. Spanning epic tales of heroism and treachery, love and war, Simonson's work is often considered the definitive Thor. From the majesty and mystery of fabled Asgard to the gritty streets of New York City, Thor was never the same. That is the mark of a true visionary. This fourth volume continues the collection of Simonson's epic run, including the unforgettable Frog Thor storyline - completely remastered from the original artwork and newly colored by Steve Oliff! Collecting THOR (1966) #364-369 and #371-374.
name: Volume 4

volume.name: The Mighty Thor By Walter Simonson
